[center][size=6][b]Personal Notes[/b][/size]
[b]An in-game note-taking system for Skyrim SE/AE[/b]

Never forget quest details, item locations, or your personal reminders again. Personal Notes lets you write and manage notes directly in-game, with full backup support.[/center]

[line]

[size=5][b]Features[/b][/size]

[size=4][b]Quest Notes[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Press [font=Courier New],[/font] (comma) while viewing a quest[/b] in the Journal Menu to add or edit a note
[*]Notes are tied to specific quests - perfect for tracking objectives, locations, or tips
[*]Visual indicator shows "Press , to add note" or "Press , to edit note"
[/list]

[size=4][b]General Notes[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Press [font=Courier New],[/font] (comma) during gameplay[/b] to create notes not tied to any quest
[*]Great for shopping lists, general reminders, or anything else
[*]Access from anywhere in the game world
[/list]

[size=4][b]Quick Access & Backup[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Press [font=Courier New].[/font] (dot) during gameplay[/b] to view all your notes in one list
[*]Browse all quest and general notes with previews
[*][b]Export all notes to JSON[/b] with one click from the quick access menu
[*]Automatic backup with timestamp and character name: [font=Courier New]Dragonborn_notes_2025-11-17_14-30-00.json[/font]
[*]Import notes from backup to restore or transfer to another character
[/list]

[size=4][b]Persistence[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Notes automatically save with your game (SKSE co-save system)
[*]Each character has separate notes
[*]Notes persist across all your saves for that character
[*]Never lose your notes when loading or saving
[/list]

