[size=5][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=4][b]dMenu UI (Recommended)[/b][/size]

If you have [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/123352][b]dMenu[/b][/url] installed, configure Personal Notes through its in-game UI:
[list]
[*]Open dMenu > Personal Notes Settings
[*]Adjust hotkeys, text size, alignment, and more
[*][b]Changes apply immediately[/b] (except hotkeys - restart required)
[*]No need to manually edit INI files
[/list]

[size=4][b]Manual Configuration[/b][/size]

Edit [font=Courier New]Data/SKSE/Plugins/PersonalNotes.ini[/font] to customize:

[b]Hotkeys:[/b]
[code]
[Hotkey]
iScanCode=51              ; Comma key (add/edit notes)
iQuickAccessScanCode=52   ; Dot key (quick access menu)
[/code]

[b]UI Customization:[/b]
[code]
[TextField]
fPositionX=5.0            ; Journal notification X position
fPositionY=5.0            ; Journal notification Y position
iFontSize=20              ; Font size for journal notification
iTextColor=16777215       ; Text color (decimal RGB)

[TextInput]
iWidth=500                ; Note editor width
iHeight=400               ; Note editor height
iFontSize=14              ; Note editor font size
iAlignment=0              ; 0=left, 1=center, 2=right
[/code]

[b]Note:[/b] Settings reload automatically when changed. Hotkeys require game restart.

[url=https://www.creationkit.com/index.php?title=Input_Script#DXScanCodes][b]DirectX Scan Code Reference[/b][/url]

[line]

[size=5][b]Usage[/b][/size]

[size=4][b]Taking Notes[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*][b]For Quest Notes:[/b] Open Journal Menu > Select a quest > Press [font=Courier New],[/font] (comma)
[*][b]For General Notes:[/b] During gameplay > Press [font=Courier New],[/font] (comma)
[*]Type your note in the text dialog
[*]Submit to save (or leave blank to delete)
[/list]

[size=4][b]Viewing All Notes[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Press [font=Courier New].[/font] (dot) during gameplay
[*]Browse the list with previews
[*]Select a note to edit it
[*]Or select "--- Export All Notes ---" to create a backup
[/list]

[size=4][b]Backup & Restore[/b][/size]

[b]Export:[/b]
[list]
[*]Press [font=Courier New].[/font] (dot) > Select "--- Export All Notes ---"
[*]Backup saved to: [font=Courier New]Data/SKSE/Plugins/PersonalNotes/backup/[/font]
[*]Filename format: [font=Courier New]<CharacterName>_notes_<timestamp>.json[/font]
[/list]

[b]Import:[/b]
[list]
[*]Copy a backup JSON file to: [font=Courier New]Data/SKSE/Plugins/PersonalNotes/import/notes.json[/font]
[*]Load any save > notes automatically imported and merged
[*]Import file is deleted after successful import
[/list]

