[line]

[size=5][b]Tips[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Empty notes are deleted[/b] - leave the text blank and submit to remove a note
[*][b]Backup regularly[/b] - use quick access to export your notes
[*][b]Transfer notes[/b] - export from one character, import to another
[*][b]Each character is isolated[/b] - starting a new game gives you a fresh slate
[*][b]Notes are per-save[/b] - each character's saves share the same notes
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]No conflicts[/b] - uses SKSE co-save system, no ESP/ESM file
[*][b]Safe to install/uninstall[/b] mid-playthrough
[*]Works with any quest mod or load order
[/list]

[b]Note:[/b] Some mods with hotkeys (e.g., Wheeler) may still trigger when editing notes. This is because those mods don't check for modal dialogs. Personal Notes blocks its own hotkeys correctly when the note editor is open.

